<section class=" bg-white py-5">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="row justify-content-center align-items-center">
      <div class="col-lg-6 mt-5 mt-lg-0 mt-0">
        <p class="lead text-dark mb-3 ">Hi! I'm <a href="https://shey.ca">Shey</a>. I really like open-source, it's a great learning tool.</p>
        <p class="mb-3">
          When I restarted my Ruby on Rails journey in 2021, I regularily visited <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20210905131349/https://opensourcerails.org/" target="_blank">opensourcerails.org</a>. It was a an easy way to find examples of how people were building their rails apps.
        </p>
        <p class="mb-3">
          At some point, the original site went down, and I missed it. So I put together this third iteration to keep that spirit alive for anyone else who learns by reading code.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
